President Donald Trump will be traveling to Peru next month to attend the Summit of the Americas in Lima. He will also meet with Peruvian President Pedro Pablo Kuczynski. After the summit, Trump will travel to Colombia to meet with President Juan Manuel Santos. This will be Trump's first trip to Latin America, and he will engage in various bilateral, multilateral, and cultural activities. The trip aims to strengthen historical ties with the region and enhance joint efforts to improve security and prosperity for the people of the Americas. Trump is eager to meet with partners and allies who share the values of strong democracies, fair trade, and secure borders.